SUMMARY:Goal Setting: Giving Direction to Your Dreams
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/goal-setting-giving-direction-to
 -your-dreams-tickets-49055710952\n\nIf you are not now making the progre
 ss youd like to make and are capable of making\, it is simply because yo
 ur goals are not clearly defined. Paul J. Meyer\nGoal setting seems easy
   yet it must be hard because so few people do it. Even people who have 
 set goals and achieved them in the past often stop setting goals for the
 mselves.\nGoals inspire you and move you forward to your lifes purpose\,
  vision and desires. Many fail to achieve their goals because they are r
 eally working on tasks and or stuff that bogs them down.\nIn this worksh
 op you will learn:\n\nTo reactivate your dream machine and review your W
 heel of Life\n5 keys to successful goal setting\nSuccessful components o
 f your goal setting Plan of Action\nHow to use affirmations and visualiz
 ation as tools to support goal setting\n\nJoin us and set new goals or j
 ump-start your old goal-setting machine from the past. Finish 2018 stron
 g  and set yourself up for even more success in 2019.\nPresenter:Jennife
 r Leake\, CEO\,Perform for Profit\n\nOver 20 years ago\, Jennifer Leake 
 launched her consulting career as a franchisee for Success Motivation In
 stitute (SMI)\, teaching goal setting\, time management\, sales and lead
 ership to those seeking to create new habits for greater personal succes
 s. These habits are timeless and still relevant\, and she attributes muc
 h of what she has achieved to the SMI goal setting principles she learne
 d.\nJennifer is the CEO of Perform for Profit\, a three-woman consulting
  firm based in Roanoke. Their mission is to help organizations and peopl
 e to Be Wildly Successful by focusing on three areas: developing strong 
 people\, accelerating business and personal performance\, and increasing
  profits. Shes an expert in employee assessments\, helping people to cho
 ose and use them to hire\, develop and retain key talent with employee e
 ngagement and emotional intelligence.\nThis event is free and open to th
 e public. Participants should bring a bagged lunch\, dessert and drinks 
 will be provided. Free parking will be provided in the student parking l
 ots. View directions and parking information.\nThe Professional Developm
 ent Exchange at Roanoke Higher Education Center (founded in spring 2018 
 by Virginia Tech/Roanoke Center) includes as its members Mary Baldwin Un
 iversity\, Radford University\, Roanoke Higher Education Center Administ
 rative Team\, The University of Virginia and Virginia Tech.
