SUMMARY:Catching Up With Cataloging
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/catching-up-with-cataloging-tick
 ets-48652524009\n\nThis full-day classisa hands-onintroduction to the pr
 ocess and components of cataloging including the reason for cataloging\,
 copy cataloging\, bibliographic description in RDA\, MARC encoding\, sub
 ject analysis\, and authority records. This class is designed for librar
 y staff without formal classroom training in cataloging and/or those who
  want to refresh their understanding of cataloging basics. This class be
 gins at 9:00 a.m. with a one hour break for lunch (provided)\, and concl
 udes by 4:00 p.m.This is abring your own device(BYOD) workshop.Participa
 nts should bring a fully-charged laptop for their useduring the workshop
 .\nPresenter:SoniaArcher-Capuzzo\nDr. Archer-Capuzzo teaches for UNCG\, 
 the State Library of North Carolina\, ALA Editions\, and several library
  associations. She has cataloged for UNCG\, Catawba County Public Librar
 ies\, and Backstage Library Works. Archer-Capuzzo studies and writes abo
 ut music librarianship\, online education\, cataloging\, and other music
 - and library-related topics\, and is working long-term on a comprehensi
 ve biography of cellist Lev Aronson. She teaches courses on information 
 organization and access\, cataloging and classification\, and music libr
 arianship.\n
